---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
	title="Getting Started"
	description="Learn how to join Madison Mesh — get hardware, install software, and send your first message on the mesh network."
>
	<div class="container">
		<section class="section" style="padding-top: 2rem;">
			<h1>Getting Started</h1>
			<p class="text-muted">
				Everything you need to go from zero to your first message on the network. You&rsquo;ll need a LoRa
				radio ($35&ndash;$50) and about an hour of setup time.
			</p>
		</section>

		<!-- Step overview -->
		<section class="section" style="padding-top: 0;">
			<div class="steps">
				<!-- Step 1 -->
				<div class="step">
					<div class="step-number">1</div>
					<div class="step-body">
						<h3>Join the community (optional but recommended)</h3>
						<p>
							The best place to get help is our
							<a href="https://discord.gg/fd3JUZc2CN" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
								>Discord server</a
							>. Members can point you to local resources, help troubleshoot hardware, and let you
							know where active nodes are located in Madison. Come say hi before you even buy
							hardware!
						</p>
						<a
							href="https://discord.gg/fd3JUZc2CN"
							target="_blank"
							rel="noopener noreferrer"
							class="btn btn-secondary"
						>
							<svg
								xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
								viewBox="0 0 127.14 96.36"
								style="height:16px;width:auto;"
								aria-hidden="true"
							>
								<path
									fill="currentColor"
									d="M107.7 8.07A105.15 105.15 0 0 0 81.47 0a72.06 72.06 0 0 0-3.36 6.83 97.68 97.68 0 0 0-29.11 0A72.37 72.37 0 0 0 45.64 0a105.89 105.89 0 0 0-26.25 8.09C2.79 32.65-1.71 56.6.54 80.21a105.73 105.73 0 0 0 32.17 16.15 77.7 77.7 0 0 0 6.89-11.11 68.42 68.42 0 0 1-10.85-5.18c.91-.66 1.8-1.34 2.66-2a75.57 75.57 0 0 0 64.32 0c.87.71 1.76 1.39 2.66 2a68.68 68.68 0 0 1-10.87 5.19 77 77 0 0 0 6.89 11.1 105.25 105.25 0 0 0 32.19-16.14c2.64-27.38-4.51-51.11-18.9-72.15ZM42.45 65.69C36.18 65.69 31 60 31 53s5-12.74 11.43-12.74S54 46 53.89 53s-5.05 12.69-11.44 12.69Zm42.24 0C78.41 65.69 73.25 60 73.25 53s5-12.74 11.44-12.74S96.23 46 96.12 53s-5.04 12.69-11.43 12.69Z"
								></path>
							</svg>
							Join the Discord
						</a>
					</div>
				</div>

				<hr class="divider" />

				<!-- Step 2 -->
				<div class="step">
					<div class="step-number">2</div>
					<div class="step-body">
						<h3>Choose your technology</h3>
						<p>
							Madison Mesh currently supports two LoRa networking platforms. We recommend
							<strong>MeshCore</strong> for most beginners, especially for text messaging.
						</p>

						<div class="card-grid" style="margin-top: 1rem;">
							<div class="card">
								<h3 style="color: var(--clr-secondary);">MeshCore</h3>
								<p style="font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">
									Best for <strong>text message communication</strong>. Client-relay
									architecture provides better range and reliability for messaging. This is
									our primary network.
								</p>
								<p class="text-muted" style="margin-bottom: 0;">
									<a href="https://meshcore.co.uk/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
										>meshcore.co.uk &rarr;</a
									>
								</p>
							</div>
							<div class="card">
								<h3>Meshtastic</h3>
								<p style="font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">
									Best for <strong>map/GPS tracking and sensor data</strong> (weather, air quality,
									etc.). Larger global community and more device options.
								</p>
								<p class="text-muted" style="margin-bottom: 0;">
									<a href="https://meshtastic.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
										>meshtastic.org &rarr;</a
									>
								</p>
							</div>
						</div>

						<p style="margin-top: 1rem;" class="text-muted">
							Both platforms support much of the same hardware, so your radio purchase won&rsquo;t
							lock you in. We recommend starting with MeshCore to help grow our local network.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<hr class="divider" />

				<!-- Step 3 -->
				<div class="step">
					<div class="step-number">3</div>
					<div class="step-body">
						<h3>Get hardware</h3>
						<p>
							You need a LoRa radio with a compatible chip (typically Semtech SX1262 or SX1276).
							Popular options in the $35&ndash;$50 range include:
						</p>
						<ul style="color: var(--clr-light); padding-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
							<li>
								<strong>Heltec V3</strong> &mdash; popular, has built-in display, good for beginners.
							</li>
							<li>
								<strong>LilyGo T-Beam</strong> &mdash; has GPS built-in, great for portable/mobile
								use.
							</li>
							<li>
								<strong>RAK WisBlock</strong> &mdash; modular system, good for fixed installations.
							</li>
							<li>
								<strong>Seeed SenseCAP Card Tracker</strong> &mdash; compact card-sized form factor.
							</li>
						</ul>
						<p class="text-muted">
							Ask in the Discord for current community recommendations &mdash; hardware evolves
							quickly!
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<hr class="divider" />

				<!-- Step 4 -->
				<div class="step">
					<div class="step-number">4</div>
					<div class="step-body">
						<h3>Install the software / firmware</h3>

						<p><strong>For MeshCore:</strong></p>
						<ol style="color: var(--clr-light); padding-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
							<li>
								Visit the <a
									href="https://flasher.meshcore.co.uk/"
									target="_blank"
									rel="noopener noreferrer">MeshCore Web Flasher</a
								> (Chrome/Edge required).
							</li>
							<li>Connect your device via USB and select your device model.</li>
							<li>Click <em>Flash</em> and wait for the process to complete.</li>
							<li>
								Download the <strong>MeshCore app</strong> for your phone (<a
									href="https://apps.apple.com/app/meshcore/id6477764842"
									target="_blank"
									rel="noopener noreferrer">iOS</a
								> /
								<a
									href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.meshcore"
									target="_blank"
									rel="noopener noreferrer">Android</a
								>) or use the desktop companion.
							</li>
						</ol>

						<p><strong>For Meshtastic:</strong></p>
						<ol style="color: var(--clr-light); padding-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
							<li>
								Visit the <a
									href="https://flasher.meshtastic.org/"
									target="_blank"
									rel="noopener noreferrer">Meshtastic Web Flasher</a
								>.
							</li>
							<li>Connect via USB, select your device, and click <em>Flash</em>.</li>
							<li>
								Download the <strong>Meshtastic app</strong> for your phone (<a
									href="https://apps.apple.com/app/meshtastic/id1586432531"
									target="_blank"
									rel="noopener noreferrer">iOS</a
								> /
								<a
									href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.geeksville.mesh"
									target="_blank"
									rel="noopener noreferrer">Android</a
								>).
							</li>
						</ol>
					</div>
				</div>

				<hr class="divider" />

				<!-- Step 5 -->
				<div class="step">
					<div class="step-number">5</div>
					<div class="step-body">
						<h3>Configure channels and connect</h3>
						<p>
							Open the app and pair it with your radio over Bluetooth or USB. Then join the Madison
							Mesh channel so your device can communicate with other local nodes.
						</p>
						<p>
							The default channel/frequency for our region is the
							<strong>US 915 MHz</strong> band. Ask in the
							<a href="https://discord.gg/fd3JUZc2CN" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
								>Discord</a
							>
							for the current channel preset and PSK used by the local network.
						</p>
						<p>
							Once configured, place your node near a window or outside for the best range.
							Elevation makes a significant difference with LoRa antennas!
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<hr class="divider" />

				<!-- Step 6 -->
				<div class="step">
					<div class="step-number">6</div>
					<div class="step-body">
						<h3>Say hello!</h3>
						<p>
							Once you&rsquo;re on the network, send a message on the public channel and introduce
							yourself. Then hop into the
							<a href="https://discord.gg/fd3JUZc2CN" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
								>Discord</a
							>
							and let us know you&rsquo;re live &mdash; we&rsquo;d love to know where new nodes pop up!
						</p>
						<a
							href="https://discord.gg/fd3JUZc2CN"
							target="_blank"
							rel="noopener noreferrer"
							class="btn btn-primary"
						>
							Join the Discord &rarr;
						</a>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>
	</div>
</Layout>
